--> an unwanted or unexcepted event that disturb normal flow of execution 

1.syntax error 

2.logical error 

Types of error:- 

1.ValueError 

2.TypeError 

3.IndexError 

4.ImportError 

5.IndentationError 

             BaseException 

 

            Exception 

ValueError         TypeError       IndexError  etc 

 

Class MyError(Exception): 

     Pass 

try and except---> are keyword 

Syntax:- 

 

try: 

      Block of code which cause error 

except:  

    If any error in try block except block will execute 

else: 

    If no error  in try block else block will execute 

    else is optional 

Print ------ 

------ 

------- 

Handling exception with error name 

try: 

    Error code 

exception ZeroDivisionError: 

      Block will handle only zero division error 

exception ValueError: 

      Only value error 

 

Try,except,else with finally block 

finally:-keyword 

finally block will execute always. 

 

Raise:- 

raise is keyword  raise our own error 

 

 

lambda function: 

--> anonymous function[no name] 

---> one line of code  

---> n number of argument but only one expression is allowed. 

Eg:- 

Res=lambda arg : expression 

Print(Res(arg)) 

 

